summary: This document details a forensic examination conducted by Victoria Tenpenny on an Apple iPhone XS as part of an investigation related to the Epstein case. The extraction was performed under legal authority, and the results were saved and returned to the assigned examiner. The document does not contain recommendations or conclusions from the FBI.

keyFacts: A forensic examination was conducted on an Apple iPhone XS.
The examination was performed by Victoria Tenpenny on July 18, 2019.
The extraction was done using GrayKey v1.11.7.
All extraction files were copied to an external hard drive.
The document states it contains no recommendations or conclusions from the FBI.
